# Testing Rules

## Required

- `pytest-httpx` for Ozon, OpenAI, AmoCRM HTTP
- `tmp_path` for idempotency store, pipeline `output_dir`, `JOB_DB_PATH`
- Mock env via `Settings(...)` or `monkeypatch.setenv` in API tests
- API: `with TestClient(create_app()) as client:` — lifespan must run
- Scale tests: mock Postgres/Redis/Celery — no real services in unit tests

## Test files (v0.5)

| File | Scope |
|------|-------|
| `test_api.py` | health, ready, auth, rate limit, jobs, metrics |
| `test_job_repository.py` | SQLite CRUD |
| `test_job_runner.py` | thread pool success/failure |
| `test_prod_hardening.py` | prerequisites, atomic IO, LLM soft-fail |
| `test_scale.py` | factories, Celery, Postgres/Redis mocks, OTEL |
| `test_coverage.py` | edge branches |

## Coverage

`pytest --cov=marketplace_pipeline` — threshold **95%** in `pyproject.toml`.

CI installs `.[dev,scale]`.

See [docs/TESTING.md](../../docs/TESTING.md).
